sentences: Dohzi-T (童子-T, Dōji Tī, born Mitsuru Takesue (竹末 充, Takesue Mitsuru), May 13, 1969) is a Japanese rapper, singer and songwriter who has been active since 1989.
Since he has long career in Japan, he is called "Brother Dohzi" by other musicians.
Dohzi-T and DJ Bass were featured in Ayumi Hamasaki's song "Nothing from Nothing", released by Nippon Columbia on September 21, 1995.
In January 2008, he collaborated with Thelma Aoyama in a song "This Day" on her CD single "Soba ni Iru ne".
In June 2008, he released his single "Mō Ichi do...", featuring Beni.
